<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-011-154 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 485 036</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 15 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>BellSouth announces ISDN plans. (Integrated Services DigitalNetworks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   BellSouth Corp. (Services).andO;Topic:     Communications Service SuppliersTelecommunications ServicesTelephone companiesIntegrated services digital networksDigital communicationsBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BellSouth Announces ISDN Plans 11/15/91 ATLANTA, GEORGIA, U.S.A., NOV 15 (NB)-- In a briefing for the press and large customers, BellSouth discussed itsplans for introducing digital services under ISDN standards to major marketsin the Southeast.andP;  The company said its first international customer for thenew service will be Fujitsu, which will use digital lines for Group 4 faxtransmissions from Atlanta to Tokyo.andM;Applications demonstrated at the briefing were mainly real-world and securityrelated.andP;  A system was shown to verify employee identifications, and foraccessing maps remotely.andP;  Systems to link local area networks and shareprinters were also shown.andP;  The announcement follows years of technical andmarket trials, and service began November 15 under the name Essx ISDN.andM;BellSouth's briefing comes about two years after Ameritech began implementingISDN service commercially in the Chicago area.andP;  There, Ricoh has for someyears been handling Group 4 fax transmissions to Tokyo.andP;  Other applicationsfor the technology include the recording of TV announcements overhigh-quality digital circuits and videoconferencing.andP;  Surprisingly, however,one of the main test centers for Ameritech's ISDN trials, McDonald's, decidednot to go with the technology, preferring the limited use of long-distancedigital circuits like ATandamp;T's Accunet.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19911115/Press Contact: Karen Mangum, BellSouth,404-529-6514)</TEXT></DOC>